                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.113/3883</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Edwards</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/> [<hi rend="italic"
                                >Ciudad Juarez</hi>] <hi rend="italic">El Paso, Texas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-01-23T19:00:00-07:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 23, 1916, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s January 21, 6 p.m. It is not advisable to allow munitions of war
                    into this district. Conditions bordering on anarchy at this time.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwards</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
